column5: ......or many others for that matter!!  Out with Terry today on GBay from 9am to about 4:15. Water temp is about 46/47F.  Terry had one nice hard rip (in 27 feet of water) at about 9:20. That was it for the day.. other than this good fight Terry had.
yeah you might say the fishing was slow  but it was still a good day on the water
Sounds much like our day yesterday on Quinte - oh well -better days ahead. I't still nice to get out on the water.  Don
Not sure about that Don.... is what is says on my Fathers Tombstone.  "There are better days ahead". Now why my Mother picked that... I'll never know!
Full windshield and gloves   what wimps LOL   Actualy I had the mitts on today , sure was windy Boys.  Sorry to hear you didn't have much action , still lots of time  TB
HAHA Dave... it was brisk out there. -3C to start the day and blowing pretty good. We came back across the open sound in 5 to 6 footers.
sounds like the weather a couple of weeks back , at least it wasn't raining ! TB

You'll get'em next time. So much for that nice day the weather network predicted 2 days ago, lol,  still says 15-16 degrees all week now, we'll see.  You guys left at the best time of day ? were you getting cold out there.
no I had to get home......I think Wayne would have stayed for hours more.......

I think we did John... there was a minor moon phase from 10:09 to 11:09 and a major from 3:52 to 5:52. We got to fish them both... well 15 minutes of the major anyhow...... so Terry could get home before dark. Something about a child hood tramatic experience... LOL
ah...it was dark before I got to midland 2 eye surgeries  and now driving in the dark is not the most fun part of the day  but it does make for an interesting time
Wayne, this day seems vaguely similar to one we had a few months ago
Hey, it happens.  At least Terry got the adrenaline flowing for awhile.  You sure it wasn't a sheephead you lost Terry  Joey
